# 3. 集う仲間たち

Nene: (Thank goodness... The others really helped get my script together.)
Nene: (But I still have a mountain of work left.)
Nene: (For now, I need to focus on recruiting. I need a cast, songwriters, people to play in the band... I'm also gonna need costume and set designers...)
???: Kusanagi?
Nene: Huh...?
Nene: M-Momoi?!
Airi: I thought it was you! Fancy seeing you here!
Airi: Also, sorry if I startled you. You didn't move after the walk light turned green, so I was wondering if everything was okay.
Nene: Huh? Oh, you're right...
Nene: Sorry, I didn't notice at all. I have a lot on my mind right now...
Airi: A lot on your mind? Is something bothering you?
Nene: No, nothing's bothering me... I just have a big laundry list of things to do at the moment.
Nene: And I'm trying to figure out how to get through it.
Airi: Then, can you tell me more about what you're doing?
Nene: Huh?
Airi: Because it's easy to get stuck while trying to solve everything on your own, right?
Airi: Talking to someone else can help clear things up. So, Kusanagi, tell me what's on your mind!
Nene: Momoi...
Nene: Thank you. So, the thing is...
Airi: I see... And you're trying to find people to join you right now.
Nene: Yes. The other planning committee members helped me make posters to put up, but I'm still having a hard time recruiting...
Airi: Yeah, being in a musical doesn't exactly sound like the easiest thing...
Airi: But I'm sure people will be interested after you tell them what you're doing.
Airi: I just happen to have a few targets in mind!
Nene: R-Really...?!
Nene: Umm... Would it be possible for you to introduce them to me?!
Airi: Sure thing! I'll try asking my friends who play music or are in arts clubs!
Nene: ...! I really appreciate it!
Airi: Then, let's exchange contact info! I'll tell anyone who agrees to help how to get a hold of you...
Nene: Oh...
Airi: Hm? Is something wrong?
Nene: Oh, no... It's just... You don't have to if you don't want to.
Nene: But is there any way I could have you join this show's cast...?
Airi: Wait, me?
Nene: So... Do you remember the show we did on top of that mountain for New Year's? You seemed to have a lot of fun while dancing, and your ad-libbing was perfect...
Nene: Oh, but I know you're really busy as an idol, so you don't have to if you can't...!
Airi: You know, since you're offering, why not? I'm in!
Nene: What? A-Are you sure?
Airi: Yeah. I'll have to check with Haruka, the others and our manager, but I should be able to pencil it into my schedule. We're actually a little free right now.
Airi: Also...
Airi: I really like the idea behind your musical. I think it's going to be wonderful.
Airi: The story of a girl who's encouraged by her musician friends to take steps towards making her dream come true.
Airi: My goal as an idol is to spread hope to others, so that really strikes a chord with me!
Nene: ...!
Nene: I appreciate you saying that. My friends and I worked really hard on this story...
Airi: Oh, but I don't have any formal acting experience, so you'll need to show me the ropes.
Nene: Of course!
Airi: Then, I'll run it by our manager and the others. We'll talk again later! See you!
Nene: (Thank goodness... Momoi agreed to help.)
Nene: (But I can't rely on her for everything. I need to look for more people on my own, too.)
Nene: (So, for now... I should try asking some of my classmates.)
Nene: (Who else might be interested?)
Nene: ...which is why I'd like you two to join the cast of our show. What do you two think, Shiraishi, Shinonome?
An: Are you talking the show from the poster that's up at the entrance? I'm in! I really wanna join!
An: I'd been thinking about it already, actually. Singing with kids from the other schools sounds super fun!
Akito: Yeah... I appreciate you inviting me to sing with you guys...
Akito: But I'm not sure how I feel about doing a musical. Really not my wheelhouse.
An: Yeah, good point. I really can't see you belting an “I Am” song on stage, Akito.
Akito: Quiet, you.
Akito: Anyway, I'm gonna have to pass. But let me know if there's anything else I can do to help. These kinds of things always involve some kind of manual labor, right?
Nene: Oh, in that case, would you mind helping us move stuff the day of? We're still a bit shorthanded there...
Akito: Yeah, no problem. It should make for a good workout.
Nene: Thanks, you two.
Nene: (Some of my classmates have already agreed to help design costumes and the set, which just leaves...)
Nene: Hey, do you guys know anyone who can write songs?
Akito: Write songs?
Nene: *Nod* If possible, I'd like to have some original songs to go with our original script.
An: Oh, then, what about Toya? He's really good at writing and arranging songs!
Akito: Yeah, he might be interested in writing songs for your show.
Nene: I see...
Nene: Thanks for telling me. I'll try asking him later.
Toya: I see. Writing songs for a musical...
Toya: Okay. If you think I'm the right person, then I'll help.
Nene: R-Really?
Toya: It's going to be my first time writing songs for a musical, but it'll be good experience for me to broaden my skillset.
Nene: Thank goodness... I really appreciate it, Aoyagi.
Mizuki: Heh heh heh. I couldn't help but overhear your guys' conversation.
Nene: Huh?! A-Akiyama?
Mizuki: So, do you plan on making your own costumes for this musical?
Nene: Y-Yeah, that's the plan...
Mizuki: Then, can I also join the team?!
Nene: Huh? That'd be huge, but are you sure?
Mizuki: Absolutely! These kinds of costumes always include a bunch of frills and lace, so designing them should be a blast!
Nene: I see. Then, welcome aboard.
Mizuki: Yay! Toya, I know we won't be working on the same stuff, but let's do our best!
Toya: Yes, let's.
Nene: (I didn't think this many people would agree to help...)
Nene: (Now I'm really glad that I went out of my way to talk to them.)
Nene: (But there's still a ton left to do.)
Nene: (For the sake of everyone who agreed to help, I have to keep on working hard!)
